The couple’s defence lawyer said there were gaping inconsistencies in the witness accounts.

He also said the pair could not have been having sex because Blake was on her period at the time, adding: ‘This is Dubai, not a mosque. Everyone drinks.’

Neither witness gave evidence in the trial. Their statements were instead submitted to judges in the misdemeanours court. 

Blake and McRedmond denied having consensual sex and indecency. They previously pleaded guilty to consuming alcohol and were fined £512.

